commit.message: Fixes links in documentation
local development setup documentation now uses correct namespace

Adapt logic to work with new deletion confirmation flow

- Remove DeletionConfirmation feature gate
- Completely rely on a set deletion timestamp

Add feature gates to gardener

Feature gates are added to the APIServer and Controller Manager, allowing to
toggle beta / alpha features.

Two Features are added:

- DeletionConfirmation which changes the way resources in the Gardener APIServer
are deleted.
- CoreDNS which changes the kubernetes DNS provider to CoreDNS.
Add Kubernetes Development guide link.

Compute dedicated OpenVPN TLS auth key per Shoot

* This requires that the controller-manager can execute the `openvpn` binary.
* The Docker image of the controller-manager is extended by the `openvpn` binary.
* The local-setup guide has been extended with instructions how to install the `openvpn` binary.

Add test for nip.io NS resolution.

For some ISPs `nip.io` is not working at all.
fix typos in comments

Rename vagrant to local

This will allow to change local implementations to support other providers than
Vagrant.

Added defaulting for .spec.cloud.local.networks

Add etcd backup restore support for aws & azure

Signed-off-by: Swapnil Mhamane <swapnil.mhamane@sap.com>

Validate Shoot/project name length sum

We use the identifier "shoot-<project-name>-<shoot-name> in nearly all places: when creating infrastructure
resources, Kubernetes resources, DNS names, etc. Some infrastructure resources have length constraints that
this identifier must not exceed 30 characters, thus we need to check whether Shoots do not exceed this limit.
The project name is a label on the namespace. If it is not found, the namespace name itself is used as project
name.
revert minikube version to 1.9.3 due to breaking cm change
Aggregated apisever requires at least 1.9.x

Guide for running Gardener on Minikube

The following scenario is supported - running the Gardener control plane
components in Minikube and running the vagrant-provider on the host machine for
creation of Shoot clusters locally. This setup simplifies the initial deployment
setup.

Remove Private- and CrossSecretBinding objects

The named objects are removed in favour of the new SecretBinding objects.
See 57ea67bd7b49e2df46ce10c0dbc3526afd9e1c72 for details.

Introduce SecretBinding resource

- SecretBindings are going to be replace PrivateSecretBindings and CrossSecretBindings.
- SecretBindings are used to bind Secrets of the same or other namespaces. They can optionally also bind Quota objects of the same or other namespaces.
- The ResourceReferenceManager admission plugin authorizes CREATE or UPDATE requests on SecretBindings which want to reference a Secret. It only allows references to secret X in namepace Y if the user is allowed to GET secret X in namespace Y.

Use platform-agnostic kubeconfig base64

Fix vagrant documentation and remove dead code
Enable Ignition, shoot deletion

Gardner Vagrant Provider implementation and docs

The `gardener-vagrant-provider` executable is a simple `GRPC` service, which
runs on the developer's machine and it's responsible for creation of Shoot
cluster's VMs. It's main target is to test the Gardener without the need to get
a Cloud Provider account and credentials.

The `gardener-controller-manager` now can talk to this service and provision
/ delete machines during the `DeployInfrastructure` / `DestroyInfrastructure` step.

The development setup for `gardener-vagrant-provider` adds an additional optional
step to the local dev setup.

Allow to run the CI scripts locally

- Run `go build` with CGO disabled
- Only create symbolic link if SOURCE_PATH is not already pointing to a Go workspace
- Change VERSION to 0.1.0-dev

The Makefile has been adapted to run the scripts in the .ci folder to avoid duplicating code.
Most important changes:
- `make dev-apiserver` has been renamed to `make start-api`.
- `make dev` has been renamed to `make start`.
- `make build` builds the apiserver and the controller manager binaries for the target environment/architecture.
- `make build-local` builds the apiserver and the controller manager binaries for the local environment/architecture.
- `make release` releases a new version of the Gardener (including building and pushing Docker images).
- The separate rules for the apiserver and controller-manager have been merged (we only want to release both components together and not indiviudally).

Shoot resource contains maintenance information

- By specifying .spec.maintenance a user can define its maintenance settings. If the section is not provided, a random maintenance time window will be computed and put into it.
- The machine types in the CloudProfiles' `.spec.*.constraints.machineTypes` section has changed: The cpus/gpus fields have been renamed to singular (similar to Kubernetes ResourceQuota object) and its internal type has been changed to resource.Quantity. This will help with the implementation of the quota admission controller.
- The status subresource and the status section have been removed from the Quota object. They are not helpful by now.
- All admission controllers do now also react on update operations.

This commit contains also minor improvements along the way.
add missing addmission controller and fix typos

documentation for complete local setup

Fix typos and remove not need blocks.
Rename garden-[apiserver|controller-manager] to gardener-[apiserver|controller-manager]

Update to [dep](https://github.com/golang/dep) v0.4.1

- Add pruning settings into Gopkg.toml
- Remove `dep prune` from `revendor` rule in Makefile (will be removed in future dep versions)
- Run `make revendor`

Fix the broken links in docs
